## **Advanced: Background Worker Integration**

If you want to offload React Fiber processing to the background worker:

```javascript
// In src/background/background.js
chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener((message, sender, sendResponse) => {
    if (message.type === 'PROCESS_VIDEO_METADATA') {
        // Heavy processing here (separate thread!)
        const metadata = processReactFiber(message.videoData);
        sendResponse({ metadata });
        return true; // Keep channel open
    }
});

// In AutoplayControlManager.js
async processVideoWithBackground(video) {
    // Quick operations on main thread
    this.processVideo(video);

    // Heavy operations on background thread
    const metadata = await chrome.runtime.sendMessage({
        type: 'PROCESS_VIDEO_METADATA',
        videoData: this.getVideoData(video)
    });

    // Use metadata...
}
